Fidelity ADT’s district manager in KwaZulu-Natal, Ivan Govender, said when leaving their cars, drivers should physically check and ensure that their cars are locked.

The extra few seconds it takes to make sure the car is properly locked and secured are worth it,” Govender said. 

He said criminals depend on their targets being distracted. 

“It is when people are not paying attention when they become easy targets for would-be thieves. The best option is therefore to be on the lookout for anyone following you or someone loitering at your car in the parking area. Trust your instincts,” he said. 

The Mercury